	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Why did he write this message? There doesn't seem to be a point, and thinking of context and timing, there is a new expansion coming out next week and usually the people at SOE are more vocal on the boards and such. It is understandable that they tried out WoW and it's nice that they paid a compliment to them, but underneath it all they must have read that NY Times article and it gave them some concern. I would still like to know why they developed EQII as a competitor to EQ1, and what they intend to do for the long term health of EQ1, especially in the area of attracting new players.<br />
<br />
I purchased the new expansion, DoN, and am not sure what I will do with it, since I am guildless atm and many of my friends on Veeshan have departed for other things such as WoW. I will keep an open mind, but I do not plan to go into the new zones and start hooking up with pick up groups, so I may be limited as to what I can do. I am one of those left behind to pick up the pieces after the release of WoW and EQII. <br />
<br />
I am enjoying WoW and have a level 43 undead warlock and now fooling around with a level 12 Dwarf Hunter, and the big difference between WoW and EQ1 is the fact that you can log on and actually do something on line for a while, especially on weeknights. This fits perfectly with someone like me who works and has a bit of time daily to do something. I think the days of logging on to a game like EQ1 and having to do a marathon session in order to progress aka large raid or dungeon crawl is over for a lot of people. WoW has not only changed the playing field, but has reset the timers and obligations for subscribers. An example of the old mindset by SOE is the recent &quot;War&quot; GM event in DL. This was done without too much warning both off line and in game, and it was done during a weeknight a bit late if your on the east coast, and from what I read this went on till the wee hours of the morning.<br />
<br />
I wish the best for EQ1..but at this point I am looking for a bit of &quot;Vision&quot; on their part. This world needs to be defined and rooted in a place for many of us to anchor to. I feel a bit adrift right now.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				Nukes R Us
			</div>
		<!-- / sig -->
		
		
		
	
	</td>
